# Docs vs knowledge separation (RULE-012)

**`docs/`** (conventional **`docs/prd/`**, **`docs/architecture/`**, **`docs/design/`**, **`docs/test/`**) is **human-readable** product narrative and **pointers** to `knowledge/catalog.yml` and primitive IDs. A repo may ship **without** `docs/` until product work begins — see **`.kfs/INDEX.md`**.

**Official KFS specs and agent procedures** live in **`.kfs/`** (`specs/`, `agent/runbooks/`). Enforceable must/must-not rules belong in **`knowledge/`** (CON/INV/CONR), not prose-only — see **`.kfs/specs/knowledge_model_spec.md`**.

## Do not in product `docs/`

- New authoritative constraints/invariants not reflected as **CON-*** / **INV-*** in `knowledge/`.
- Shadow API contracts — use **CONR-*** in `knowledge/contracts/`.

## Do in product `docs/`

- Summarize intent; link **FEAT-***, **CON-***, **INV-***, **DEC-***, **CONR-*** by ID.
- Keep PRD/HLD aligned with merged knowledge; fix doc drift after Knowledge PRs.

New “must” from review → **primitive** + **catalog** (Knowledge PR), then reference from the doc.
